{
  "version": "1.0",
  "description": "Keyword lists for classifying arXiv papers by country. Two sets per country: 'affiliation' keywords are used when an explicit affiliation field is available; 'abstract' keywords are used as a fallback against abstract text and are deliberately more specific to reduce false positives.",
  "notes": [
    "Word-boundary matching is applied to all keywords.",
    "If both US and China keywords match the same text, the paper is classified as Unknown (likely a collaboration).",
    "Keywords should be institution- or company-specific names, not country names, to avoid false positives in abstract text."
  ],

